Reasoning: The paper discusses the relativity of finiteness in computation models defined on top of toposes, which are mathematical structures used in category theory. This topic is closely related to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL), as well as information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper explores the properties of Dedekind and Kuratowski notions of finiteness, which are concepts in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
